# Auto Deploy After Every Change

After making ANY code change, always do the following without being asked:

1. `git add -A`
2. `git commit -m "<concise message>"` — single line, present tense, no heredoc (PowerShell)
3. `git push origin master`
4. Run `vercel ls` and poll until the top deployment shows `● Ready`
5. Tell the user: **"Deployed ✓"** with the age/duration from `vercel ls`

## PowerShell rules
- Never use `&&` — use `;` to chain commands
- Never use heredoc (`<<'EOF'`) — use a plain `-m "..."` string

## When to do this
- After every single task or fix, even tiny ones
- No exceptions — do not wait to be asked
